A Chinese-Russian venture will
invest 8 billion yuan ($1.27 billion) to build a small-plane
manufacturing base in  China â€™s Inner Mongolia region, Xinhua
reported today, citing a company agreement.  China Oriental Sciences Group will hold 52 percent of the
